# Cursor Rules: Debugging Protocol & Self-Learning System

This file defines two things:

- **A)** The debug log protocol (mandatory on every bug fix)
- **B)** A pre-flight checklist the AI must run before writing code

---

# A. DEBUG LOG PROTOCOL

## Rule: Mandatory Debug Logging

Every time you fix a build error, runtime crash, or resolve a bug reported by the user (including Xcode build failures, linker errors, type mismatches, missing imports, SwiftUI preview crashes, or CocoaPods/MediaPipe integration issues), you MUST append a structured entry to `DEBUG_LOG.md` at the project root BEFORE telling the user the fix is complete.

Do NOT skip this step. Do NOT summarize it verbally instead of writing it. Write to the file.

### Completeness (no misses)

- **One entry per distinct root cause.** If one session fixes several unrelated issues, write **separate entries** (each with its own DL number). If multiple symptoms share one root cause, a single entry may cover them if **Error**, **Root Cause**, and **Fix Applied** stay precise.
- **Same turn as the fix:** Append to `DEBUG_LOG.md` in the **same assistant turn** that lands the code change ‚Äî never defer logging to a follow-up message or a verbal summary.
- **User-confirmed fixes count:** If the user reports a bug and you resolve it (including after their confirmation), the log entry is still mandatory before you treat the topic as closed.
- **Verify on disk:** After editing, confirm the new `### [DL-XXX]` block is present in `DEBUG_LOG.md` (e.g. re-read the tail of the file). Chat-only descriptions are not a substitute.

### Entry Format

Use this exact format for every entry:

````markdown
---

### [DL-XXX] <Short descriptive title>
**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD  
**Severity:** critical | build-breaking | warning | cosmetic  
**Category:** <see categories below>  
**File(s):** `<affected file paths>`

**Error:**
<Exact error message or description as reported by Xcode/compiler/runtime>

**Root Cause:**
<What was actually wrong in the code. Be specific ‚Äî name the variable, the type, the missing import, the incorrect threshold. Not "there was a type mismatch" but "AngleCalculator.swift line 142 returned Optional<Double> but UniversalRepCounter expected Double, causing force-unwrap crash.">

**Fix Applied:**
<What you changed, in which file(s), and why this fixes it>

**Prevention Rule:**
<A concrete, actionable rule that ‚Äî if followed during initial coding ‚Äî would have prevented this error from occurring. Write this as an imperative instruction, e.g., "Always unwrap MediaPipe landmark confidence values with nil-coalescing (default 0.0) rather than force-unwrapping." or "When adding a new SwiftUI view file, immediately add it to the Xcode target membership ‚Äî don't assume Xcode auto-includes it.">

**Pattern Tags:** #<tag1> #<tag2>
````

### Categories (use exactly these strings)

- `swift-types` ‚Äî Type mismatches, optional handling, casting errors
- `swiftui-views` ‚Äî View body errors, property wrappers, preview crashes
- `mediapipe-integration` ‚Äî Framework linking, model loading, pipeline errors
- `cocoapods-build` ‚Äî Pod install issues, workspace config, script phases
- `xcode-config` ‚Äî Build settings, signing, entitlements, target membership
- `angle-math` ‚Äî Incorrect angle calculations, threshold logic, 2D/3D fallback
- `exercise-definitions` ‚Äî Malformed ExerciseDefinition, missing fields, wrong keys
- `concurrency` ‚Äî Main actor isolation, async/await, published property threading
- `camera-pipeline` ‚Äî AVCaptureSession, frame delivery, permissions
- `ui-layout` ‚Äî Auto Layout, safe area, overlay positioning, animations
- `state-management` ‚Äî ObservableObject, @Published, @State, @Binding issues
- `other` ‚Äî Anything not covered above

### DL Number Sequence

Read the last `### [DL-XXX]` heading in `DEBUG_LOG.md` to determine the next DL number. If there are no entries yet, use **DL-001**.

