# C. CODE REVIEW SELF-CHECK (Before Presenting Code to User)

Before presenting any code change to the user, silently run through this checklist:

- [ ] Does the code compile with strict concurrency enabled?
- [ ] Are all optionals handled safely (no force unwraps on external data)?
- [ ] Are new files in the correct directory per the module structure (Camera/, Vision/, Models/, RepCounting/, Coaching/, UI/, DesignSystem/, Services/)?
- [ ] Do new UI elements use Theme tokens (Theme.Colors, Theme.Fonts, Theme.Spacing) instead of hardcoded values?
- [ ] If I added a new view, does it respect the "No-Fluff Noir" design system?
- [ ] If I modified ExerciseLibrary.swift, are all fields present and consistent?
- [ ] Have I checked DEBUG_LOG.md for relevant Prevention Rules?

If any check fails, fix the code before presenting it.

